description: Whatever Sheila Jordan sings she makes completely her own to the point that the line between composition and interpretation is extremely blurry. Now in her late 80s, Jordan is booked for the rest of the year with performances and masterclasses across the USA, as well in Germany, Austria, Italy, and Japan. After watching Molly Sheridan's video presentation here, read Frank J. Oteri's extensive conversation with Sheila Jordan on NewMusicBox: http://www.newmusicbox.org/articles/sheila-jordan-music-saved-my-life/
title: Sheila Jordan: Music Saved My Life
fulltitle: Sheila Jordan: Music Saved My Life
